Die Transformation wird unser Leben enorm verändern, viele Menschen sind verunsichert. Wie nimmt man alle im Wandel mit? Um diese Frage drehte sich ein Forum bei #RNE2023: https://www.nachhaltigkeitsrat.de/aktuelles/was-haelt-unsere-gesellschaft-in-der-transformation-zusammen/
Debatte mit Reiner Hoffmann, Dr. Claudia Bogedan (@boeckler_de), Felix Berning (IG BAU Münster-Rheine, DBJR), Franka Bernreiter (UN-Jugenddelegierte, DBJR) & @TanjaBusse
📸Wagenzik, Domma/RNE

content:
⚠️ ANNOUCEMENT

Ok, this is akward but I decided to make a change and invert this, so that it shows a depleted percentage, rather like how a hour glass works or more directly the graphical representation of battery charge being used up on a device.

Because in my mind that is sort of what is happening here, you are actually slowly losing this day before you start again with a fresh, new full one.

If you want to follow this to see your home feed broken in 10% chunks that still works of course. 😉

content:
Dear Cthulhu, my eyes are bleeding.

This, by the way, is a prime example of highly manipulative writing.

It starts out by listing a few things that are difficult to deny.

It then *associates* other beliefs with these things, even though they are not related.

And then it continues to argue as if they were related, in a way that in itself is quite sound. It repeats this pattern several times.

This structure of argument is meant to make you believe that the *association* is actually...

content:
I think part of the disconnect between expectation and reality when it comes to the behavior of journalists on social media is that a plurality of people carrying the moniker do not primarily fill the role of journalisms, but rather specialized Public Relations.

Often as a kind of outsourced PR for the industry they cover, the "beat". Always as PR for their publications and a publishing ecosystem whose incentive structure is in conflict with their purpose.

Hence platform access journalism.

Contrast with the USA, who will require that the evacuees sign a promissory note, obligating them to repay for the transport, and will be flown not to the USA but to "the nearby safe countries", from where they will be on their own:
